Description: Three-legged wooden table; painted representation of Renenutet before offering-table and column of Hieroglyphic text on top.
Curator's comments: Published: Killen, Ancient Egyptian Furniture I, p. 67, pl. 111-13; Baker, Furniture in the Ancient World, p. 153, pl. 237; Aegyptiaca Bononiensia, 108.
Acquisition notes: Listed in 2nd edition of 1836 Salt Sale catalogue as lot 657*.
